Penis (Figs 5
c-d
). Shaft broad, tendon relatively short; bristle groups well-developed. Glans short, broad, triangular in dorsal view; in line with shaft; dorsal side evenly convex; not significantly flattened distally. Pores shallowly recessed.

Spiracle (Figs 2
c-d
). No occluding spines; lace tubercles at lateral corner reduced to patch of reticulation.
